'''Operation Sun Rising''' was a [[cold war]] military intelligence program run by the [[Inter-Services Intelligence|ISI]] or [[Pakistan]] during the late 1970s.<ref name="Political Deception">{{cite news|last=Abbasi|first=Ansari|title=Political Deception|url=http://www.thereligionislam.com/affairs/nuclearprogrammeofpakistanandcia.htm|accessdate=21 May 2013|newspaper=Political Deception}}</ref> In the 1970s, the program was launched when the ISI believed the [[President of the United States|President]] [[Jimmy Carter]]'s [[Carter administration|administration]] was planning of sabotaging and infiltrating the highly clandestine [[Pakistan and weapons of mass destruction|atomic bomb projects]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Staff|title=Exclusive|url=http://www.terminalx.org/2011/02/exclusive-does-cia-fear-another.html#ixzz2TuYwujXM|accessdate=21 May 2013|date=February 23, 2011}}</ref> The program purpose was to collect [[Intelligence cycle management|intelligence cycle]] on potential contingency plans of [[Carter administration]] sabotaging of certain bomb-related installations and facilities. The program was initiated in 1979 by [[Imtiaz Ahmed (brigadier)|Imtiaz Ahmed]], then chief of [[Intelligence Bureau (Pakistan)|Intelligence Bureau]].<ref name="Political Deception" />
The ''Sun Rising'' was downscaled with the arrest and conviction of an agent working for CIA and the declaration of a few undercover CIA agents and US diplomats as [[personae non gratae]] and their return.<ref name="Dawn News">{{cite news|last=Zaffar Abbas|title=Only bean-spilling spooks can tell why|url=http://archives.dawn.com/archives/37099|accessdate=21 May 2013|newspaper=Dawn News|date=September 1, 2009}}</ref> The program remained highly secretive for several years after its operational activities activated since 1979. The program's existence was discovered by espionage investigative journalist, [[Ansar Abbasi]] of the [[The News International|''News International'']] in 2009.<ref name="The News International">{{cite news|last=Abbasi|first=Ansar|title=Brig Imtiaz reveals CIA plots|url=http://thenews.com.pk/|accessdate=21 May 2013|newspaper=The News International|date=3 September 2009}}</ref> Since its discovery, the exact notion and nature of the program has been criticized by prominent [[News channels in Pakistan|news]] [[Media of Pakistan|media]] of Pakistan.<ref name="Dawn News" /><ref>{{cite news|title=Jilts over the program|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/-jilted-lover-saved-pak-nukes-programme-/467607/|accessdate=21 May 2013|newspaper=India Today}}</ref>
